		"description": "<p>Also at 6th level, you can sway people to your way of thinking, either with a speech, an appeal to a creatureâ€™s own cultural interests, a threat, a clever web of lies, or a musical performance. You must be proficient in Persuasion to use a speech, Insight to use an appeal, Intimidation to use a threat, Deception to use lies, or Performance to use music. All creatures of your choice within 30 feet of you must make a Wisdom saving throw against a DC equal to your clever tricks save DC.</p>\n<p>On a failed save a creature gains the [[/condition id=charmed]] condition for one minute. After one minute, and every minute thereafter, they may make another saving throw. The condition ends when the creature makes a successful saving throw.</p>\n<p>Once you have used this feature, you cannot do so again until after you have finished a long rest.</p>",
